Job Details.Description: Software engineers design, develop, and test software and applications for computers. The main duties and responsibilities of software engineers include directing and participating in programming activities, monitoring, and evaluating system performance, and designing and implementing new programs and features.

Become a professional picture framer. Frame pictures in beautiful designer frames that only the deepest of pockets can afford. Occasionally deal with the public.
        Provide clients with information on possible framing and restoration timelines and costs. Extract pictures from old frames, making sure that they are not torn or damaged, and place them carefully in new ones.

Presenter, radio and television. Presenters act as the public face (or voice) on television and radio programmes; they are responsible for introducing and interviewing guests, linking segements, and generally holding the show together.
